D.q[3952] = "";
D.q[2871] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[693] = "Hogmeiser lost his boots during a fierce fight against a Gobball War Chief, the day of Captain Chafer\'s Panty Party... I should add that he was under the influence of substances with uncommon effects.\nHe woke up the next day, totally naked in the middle of the swamp, without his boots.";
D.q[755] = "";
D.q[4854] = "The evidence against Kit Dingaround\'s treason case wasn\'t sufficient, and, as such, the case has been dismissed. Kit Dingaround shall return to his position as militiaman and will be under surveillance by another militiaman for one year.";
D.q[1398] = "...";
D.q[810] = "100";
D.q[7029] = "Show me that.\nThe seal is rotten and in this state this mask isn\'t good for anything. Luckily for you I have patches to hand.\nHop, one here, another there, a third here... There, it should be fine now.";
D.q[1030] = "/action start the fight/ (?)";
D.q[622] = "Ah, well, excellent. You\'re already a true alchemist. Keep at it, and you\'ll definitely improve. Good luck, comrade.";
D.q[6931] = "Talk about a life in a castle! When I knew him he was rich as Terrakourial, but I didn\'t know he was so stingy. After we got married, we bought the shack and started breeding Dragoturkeys. Even if business is good, my husband saves money on everything. He says we should not spend more than necessary, which for him amounts to buying the minimum we need to live on and no more.\nAll the extras, I pay with the money I make on the market square in Amakna. If I could only find out where he has hidden his fortune, we could finally live decently.";
D.q[936] = "Hello, friend, I\'m the best pyrotechnician in Bonta. If you\'re looking for any kind of explosives, I\'m your man.";
D.q[7264] = "";
D.q[614] = "My investigation was making no headway, I was just about to go round the house again when someone came into the room and called out to me...";
D.q[2526] = "Shush\n*in a low voice*\nBefore you talk to me, you must sort out this problem with the tax, because you won\'t be welcome around here until you do. That\'s why I can\'t talk to you openly. Traditions, you know. Come back and see my when you\'re sorted, we\'ll have a chat then.\nCome back when you\'ve paid and then we\'ll talk.";
D.q[1905] = "You come at the right moment! My delivery man has just fallen sick and I can\'t take care of the delivery of a special order. I need strong arms and fast legs to deliver these cakes all over the town. I\'ll pay you well, are you interested?";
D.q[7265] = "";
D.q[7363] = "";
D.q[4248] = "";
D.q[5177] = "";
D.q[1320] = "Oh, you\'re on fatigue duty? Be an angel and peel 20 spuds for me, would you? Could you bring me 6 Crow feet and 3 eyes too... for the taste, you know. Thanks in advance! And be careful not to cut yourself.";
D.q[1019] = "Well done! You didn\'t forget the beer... Always remember that a student with the thirst for knowledge must first quench the thirst of his master...heh heh! I\'ll put the card with the rest of my collection right away.";
D.q[6992] = "What are you on about? The expert in astral projection and transmission of thoughts is Magus Ax, in Astrub. I just make potions and magic scrolls, understand?";
D.q[4687] = "";
D.q[4834] = "Well I think everyone\'s here, so let\'s get started.\nI, Satirev Onivin, judge of Bonta, declare the trial of Kit Dingaround for treason open.\n(...)\nSo I ask, does Kit Dingaround\'s version of events seem credible to you or not?";
D.q[4032] = "Do you have any ingredients to give me?";
D.q[2420] = "This trade is convenient for the youngsters setting out on their journey through this harsh world. Quite an easy and cheap profession, you\'ll be mainly concerned with grinding flour for bakers.";
D.q[5410] = "Come on now, sing with me. \'When you call Bibi, he\'ll always come running. He\'s full of life and he\'s got some left over. All along the Rocky Plains, people are talking. He\'s always winning...\'\nWell, what do you want to do? Leave the dungeon? If you have a Rainbow Blop Lair Key, I can take you.";
D.q[2714] = "Our mission is to kick the adventurer vermin off our beloved island and let me tell you, the end justifies the means, that\'s our attitude. I suggest the following - sabotage bridges, steal the left shoe off anyone who looks a bit dodgy, poison the water... It\'s all good! If you wanna be one of us, you must answer this question correctly:\nEverybody knows the sound of two pints clinking together... But what sound does one pint make?";
D.q[4692] = "";
D.q[4255] = "";
D.q[4588] = "Lenalds are vely... sorry verrry friendly. If you find the one that knows most about this affair, I\'m sure you\'ll have no problem getting the details out of him.";
D.q[4693] = "";
D.q[4730] = "I\'m waiting for my Bewitched Hornbeam Wood.";
D.q[7461] = "";
D.q[6700] = "Are you in charge of this investigation? Kit is in real trouble, believe me.\nThat\'s funny, that strap tip you\'re holding matches the one taken from his bag. If you no longer need my services, go see Amayiro, I think he\'s looking for you.";
D.q[7583] = "What\'s the matter? Haven\'t you seen a very hairy woman before?";
D.q[5797] = "";
D.q[3569] = "What you need for a flag is a symbol. A symbol is not the flag... you have to sew the symbol on the flag. You know what I mean?";
D.q[5796] = "";
D.q[4589] = "I was thinking of the horn... perhaps Brakmar has gone to search for it too. That could explain why our agents have been disappearing on the Island. But that isn\'t too likely.";
D.q[4049] = "x";
D.q[6994] = "Flutterthoughts? I\'ve heard of them somewhere before, but where and when?\nWell, it should not be complicated to remember, let me think for a moment...\nThere! A happy Enutrof talked to me about them once, but I didn\'t pay any attention. Sorry.";
D.q[7832] = "Before everything froze over, I chopped wood. Now I chop animals as well, that way I protect the other lumberjacks and my friend Al Shab is happy.";
D.q[2865] = "I sent some Brakmarians to kill some of the Bontarian militia\'s Dragoturkeys and to steal from their provisions, but the idiots were scared off by the group of guards around the paddock. Afraid of being caught, they retreated and burnt the food warehouse on their way, leaving the Dragoturkeys alive and returning without a scrap of food for Brakmar. Our food supply has not been replenished.\n\nYou must go to Astrub to find Raymon Santho, a trader with ties to Bonta. Do whatever you have to win him over to our side.";
D.q[5799] = "";
D.q[3310] = "Pnj(803) et Message(3308)";
D.q[4700] = "";
D.q[4695] = "Yeah?";
D.q[5124] = "";
D.q[7584] = "The cave? What cave?\nOh, you mean that cave there... My daddy lives there. When my mummy died, he lost it completely and became extremely dangerous, both to himself and to visitors.\nThe problem is, he\'s blocking the way to the Hammer-Sickle guild\'s best mine. That\'s the reason I don\'t just let any old person go in there.";
D.q[6995] = "I am not an expert in lepidopteran insects that have two pairs of wings covered with scales, which lay eggs that become larvae, which in turn become caterpillars, then form chrysalis to turn into adults, sometimes called imago. This imago stage is characterised by the facility to procreate, unlike the larval stage. Anyway, as I said, I\'m not an expert on the subject.";
D.q[7585] = "Sorry, my daddy is asleep. You can\'t just come barging in here when you feel like it. Come back when he\'s awake.";
D.q[4047] = "x";
D.q[7833] = "You see all those trunks? Chief Anbifketf needs them for the pipes\' heating system, which will stop the port from freezing over.\nYou can take them to him if you want.";
D.q[4701] = "";
D.q[4731] = "";
D.q[2146] = "Well, she bet that the Enutrofs weren\'t brave enough to venture into the underpasses, with all that\'s been going on, you know, all the killings and stuff. On the contrary, I told her, they go there all the more, now there\'s a good chance of dying.";
D.q[7586] = "I\'ve to warn you, it\'s really dangerous in there. Are you sure you want to go in?";
D.q[633] = "Forgetfulness of Pandora\'s Box: 5  Old Four-Leaf Clover, 10 Gold Ingots, 1 Diamond, 1 Sapphire, 1 Ancestral Amber\nForgetfulness of Location: 3 Carved Bone, 20 Omniscient Crystal Staff-Ball, 1 Black Paint.\nForgetfulness of Compulsion: 4 Bloody Flints, 20 Valuable Rings, 10 Stamina Belts, 10 Iop\'s Crushers\nForgetfulness of Time Storm: 5 Everlasting Flowers, 50 Old-age Potions, 5 Dragon Pig Skulls, 10 Old dreggon Bones, 10 Unikron Blood.";
D.q[5242] = "";
D.q[2869] = "Hello, we are bankers. You can open an account here and you\'ll have a safe place in which to keep your property. Please note that each time you access your bank account, it will cost you #1 Kamas.";
D.q[4718] = "";
D.q[4151] = "So, did you manage to find the flours I need?";
D.q[5801] = "";
D.q[5153] = "...";
D.q[6936] = "You really want to know? It\'s very simple: I decided to lock her away because more and more Enutrofs were beginning to worry that she would discover where we were hiding their wealth. You might think it\'s inhumane, but I can assure you that other people wanted to use more radical methods. You might even say that it was an act of charity on my part. Being imprisoned for ten years is better than being beheaded by several shovels, don\'t you think?\nNow leave me alone, I do not want to dwell on these memories, and you\'ll get nothing from me anymore. You can always look, but you will not find the tile or its mechanism, hehe.";
D.q[5209] = "";
D.q[1149] = "Welcome to my Inn. If you want something to drink, you only have to ask for the menu...";
D.q[6996] = "I was once the greatest soul hunter of all time. Don\'t get me wrong, I didn\'t belong to the Brakmarian Order of the Putrid Eye.\nIn fact, I was looking for Dofus and capturing souls was a good way to become more powerful and get rich to pay for information about these dragon eggs.\nI was hunting the souls of creatures to sell to the highest bidder until Otomai offered me a job worthy of my talent. Indeed, he wants to unite the souls of all living creatures, and I was the first to have achieved this goal.";
D.q[7809] = "We\'ve been going round in circles for days without meeting a soul. I\'m glad you found us. Speak to Red Richard, he\'s great at finding solutions to our problems.";
D.q[4759] = "Strip teases do very little for me. Go and tell that to your judge.";
D.q[5803] = "";
D.q[6937] = "You know about it? My husband won\'t be pleased...";
D.q[6919] = "Hello, it\'s been a long time since anyone came to visit me. How did you find me?";
D.q[2986] = "I can see you\'re eloquent! don\'t hesitate to consult your star. It will tell you how you should speak to people around you. You\'ll be able to charm the opposite sex by telling them exactly how you feel and to make many, many friends... And when you\'re a bit harder, you\'ll be able to train an Adventurer Group and talk to them like a chief. You\'ll be part of a Guild and its members will listen to you!";
D.q[2984] = "Gulp! Astrub beer is my favourite! Such light bitterness, such smooth froth.....yum... G-gulp! So, I can see you were born under a lucky star. Look, you can see it on the bottom left, understand?";
D.q[4766] = "Congratulations! Everything\'s not lost yet for Kit.";
D.q[6938] = "Hmm, I think I can help you, but there has to be a little bit of give as well as take.\nIf I help you to free the medium, you must promise me you\'ll question her about where my husband hid his fortune.\nDeal?";
D.q[1934] = "Here you are, at last! You don\'t look the brightest but that will change, you\'ll see. \nTill then I\'ve something for you to do.";
D.q[5501] = "";
D.q[3085] = "Great! All we\'ve to do now is to deliver all this. Go see if Monabella is still interested.";
D.q[1693] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[7626] = "";
D.q[7267] = "";
D.q[5805] = "";
D.q[6941] = "I see, someone managed to unlock the entrance and you just happened to be passing by.\nIf you don\'t mind, I\'d like to be alone for a little while. I must admit that I am too accustomed to solitude, and seeing so many people so suddenly scares me a little.";
D.q[3706] = "Hello! Are you looking for adventure too?";
D.q[6681] = "";
D.q[3276] = "Come on! A last small effort and you\'ll be able to access the next room in one piece!";
D.q[7268] = "";
D.q[5807] = "";
D.q[4242] = "Good Day!";
D.q[5808] = "";
D.q[5806] = "";
D.q[4787] = "The militia? Who do you take me for? I had no evidence and they would have dragged me off for defamation, the clowns! What do you think? They look after themselves.";
D.q[3802] = "Well, well, I\'m sure you\'ve got something that could interest me. You\'ve got a Snoowolf skin, haven\'t you?";
D.q[4604] = "";
D.q[4772] = "";
D.q[4773] = "";
D.q[1724] = "Srams can use any weapon, but they handle daggers and bows best.";
D.q[7270] = "";
D.q[4263] = "";
D.q[1730] = "Sadidas can use any weapons, but they handle staffs and wands best.";
D.q[4813] = "";
D.q[6940] = "Now that is a very good question. An Ecaflip tourist showed up there several years ago with this tile. It set it down there, then he cast a strange spell and left as quickly as he came. Don\'t ask me why, I don\'t know.";
D.q[6999] = "I do not discuss work with people I do not know. If I get wind of any honourable or selfless acts you\'ve performed, then maybe I will change my mind.";
D.q[4703] = "What are you doing here? Me? I like hanging out with the living-dead, well, so long as they don\'t attack me.";
D.q[7271] = "";
D.q[5409] = "";
D.q[6943] = "Certainly, the loneliness was unbearable at times, and when winter came, I realised how empty this room was and that my mattress was surprisingly cold. So I prayed to the goddess Sacrier to give me the strength necessary to overcome this ordeal, and that is how I survived until today.";
D.q[7000] = "That voice... Come into the light.\nYes, I recognize you! You had to ask the medium where my husband has hidden his fortune. There\'s no point you asking me anything while you don\'t have the answer.";
D.q[2733] = "Well, well, well, someone\'s sure of themselves. Coming up to me like this. What do you want?";
D.q[4845] = "";
D.q[4840] = "";
D.q[6794] = "What do you mean? Thank you for worrying about me but all is well.";
D.q[4899] = "I\'ve never heard of such an object, but if I hear anything I\'ll let you know.";
D.q[4243] = "Bad Day!";
D.q[7001] = "That\'s not the kind of question people normally ask me. I know an expert in the field but he is being treated at the village of Pandala, at Surivitna the Shaman\'s house. His name is Meuh Sieurchance. You can not miss him, he\'s an Enutrof that\'s happy in spite of his baldness.\nIf you intend to go to Pandala, don\'t go on an empty stomach. I\'ll sell you some Dragoturkey Steak for a discount, 4,000 Kamas per kilo. What do you say?";
D.q[1357] = "*Rock*\nTough luck, you\'ve lost...";
D.q[5143] = "";
D.q[4101] = "";
D.q[4851] = "";
D.q[1292] = "Criquatis Criquatquatis Criquatis CriCri Criquatis Criciquatis";
D.q[4435] = "";
D.q[4007] = "Deal!";
D.q[6795] = "Other things? Like what, for example? If it\'s about his arrest, I\'ve already said everything.";
D.q[6945] = "I\'ll help you but I cannot control my visions. I need more detail for the divination to occur. Can you tell me more about this Spirit of Light?";
D.q[6796] = "If you hit me I\'ll call the other guards, and anyway, I don\'t know anything else.";
D.q[7665] = "I see you are surrounded by an evil aura. Tell me what you want before I take the appropriate action.";
D.q[4725] = "";
D.q[7133] = "";
D.q[4917] = "A doll? What do you take me for? Find yourself a Sadida if you want to play with dolls!\nMaskara will be delighted to do so.";
D.q[7274] = "";
D.q[5330] = "";
D.q[7273] = "";
D.q[5399] = "";
D.q[5812] = "";
D.q[7035] = "I don\'t plan to stay here forever. As it is, there\'re barely enough provisions for the return journey. If we hang around too much, we\'ll starve, if the cold and humidity haven\'t killed us first.";
D.q[7570] = "Which class temple would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[4942] = "";
D.q[7443] = "";
D.q[6946] = "I see... a dark crypt, scarlet lips with two long canines protruding from them, demented laughter in the dark.\nI feel a muscle tear, excruciating pain.\nI see a hammer sinking into darkness and light dissipating. There is a being, or rather an ethereal spirit.\nI see a cemetery, then a forest, mountains in the distance, an underground passage, a land of ash and lava.\nI see a dark graveyard, spirits in agony, a profound sadness.";
D.q[7571] = "Which class temple would you like coordinates for?";
D.q[7275] = "";
D.q[7617] = "Obviously, and that\'s why I told you you\'re too late.\nStrange Dreggon eggs, nicknamed \"Sauroshells\", starting appearing all over the peninsula and in the underground during the month of Novamaire in the year 639. Many adventurers and other apprentice Dreggon hunters began looking for them to make omelettes, which were sold for a very high price at King Allister\'s banquet.\nWhen the last Sauroshell was destroyed, Grozilla and Grasmera came out of their torpor to avenge this irrational destruction.";
D.q[5151] = "";
D.q[6947] = "Now there is a city full of eager young minds. I see a house and potions, an Eniripsa stands before them. There is also a Sadida, she is busy making a doll, but this is not a typical Sadida doll, it looks more like a Feca...\nThe vision disappears, there is nothing more.";
D.q[5334] = "";
D.q[5333] = "";
D.q[6797] = "Hey, calm down, I don\'t want to fight with you, I value my life. I\'ve already said everything about Kit Dingaround and hitting me won\'t change anything. It\'s not that I don\'t want to help you, I just don\'t know anything else";
D.q[7276] = "";
D.q[5813] = "";
D.q[7567] = "I put my preparation in the flask, I add the petal, and I mix it together.\nThere, that should do the trick. If the cure works, I should be able to create a lot more very easily.";
D.q[7004] = "I\'ll try to heal him using the Sacred Water of the Goddess Pandawa and a Dontase Mebro Shovel. This is a rather violent treatment but his condition leaves us no choice.";
D.q[1284] = "Have a drink if you\'re a real warrior! Heheh!";
D.q[7003] = "So far, my remedies have only worsened Meuh Sieurchance\'s condition. He\'s now in quarantine and is forbidden from going out. I can\'t leave my patients unattended, so if you like, you can help me get his memory back.";
D.q[6799] = "I know nothing more, even a purse of one million Kamas cannot change that. I\'m sorry.";
D.q[763] = "53";
D.q[7834] = "Hello, behind me is a place as cold as Jiva\'s heart and as sharp as the blade of Iop\'s sword.\nYou go in there at your own risk, I\'m telling you.";
D.q[7277] = "";
D.q[5393] = "";
D.q[5815] = "";
D.q[767] = "57";
D.q[5814] = "";
D.q[7005] = "In the village of Akwadala, there is a house with access to an underground spring where, over the course of a thousand and one nights, the goddess Pandawa bathed in order to purify herself. The entrance can be opened by three Pandawas who master the spell \'Wrath of Zatoishwan\'. Recruit the Pandawas you need and fetch two buckets of water.";
D.q[3782] = "Do you wish to return to your statue, young one?";
D.q[6800] = "I\'m not afraid of anything, I have no reason to be afraid.";
D.q[2523] = "So Grandapan asked me to offer his prayers to Pandawa, our beloved goddess? This a sacred mission... Come with me!";
D.q[4719] = "A farmer\'s work is tough, but as I\'m the youngest member of the family, I don\'t have to work in the fields every day. \nWhen I\'m bigger I\'m gonna be a Bonta militiaman too.";
D.q[7278] = "";
D.q[5394] = "";
D.q[7836] = "Do you want to go back up again?";
D.q[7564] = "It\'s distilled Ouassingue Juice. It\'s forbidden in all of the world\'s civilised cities because it causes anyone who drinks it to become hopelessly addicted.\nNow you\'ve got what you wanted, go pester someone else.";
D.q[2344] = "You want a pair of scissors that I\'ve carved myself? Hmm, that pretty girl Resserd has broken hers again, right?\nWell, I\'ll need three pieces of iron, but I\'m out of iron right now... ask a miner, he\'ll help you to find some. If you find what I need, I\'ll make your scissors for free!";
D.q[132] = "Xavier the Baker is very famous in Baking circles. All this attention he\'s getting... he thinks he\'s the greatest thing since sliced bread. I\'m the one with charisma, I\'m the one with the crusty bread... Everything they say about him is fibs. Plus they all think I\'m jealous, well I\'m not!";
D.q[6472] = "There could be several reasons for that. Let me see... you\'re ugly, you\'ve got bad breath, no class. You\'re a terrible cook. Your equipment stinks... well you see what I mean. Maybe he just like men better. Or Arachnees... who knows!";
D.q[7837] = "Look at you, you\'re soaked to the bone. If you go out in that state, you\'ll catch your death.\nUse this towel to dry yourself off a bit... That\'s better, I can let you out now.";
D.q[6801] = "Me, afraid? Why should I be afraid? No, I\'m not afraid.";
D.q[6193] = "";
D.q[1351] = "*Waves his hand*";
D.q[6802] = "I gave you the description of the man who was speaking to Kit Dingaround on the day of his arrest, I do not know anything else.";
D.q[6426] = "Heyyy, calm down, I don\'t want any trouble here. The Ecaflips were talking about a hideout somewhere in the Cania Plains, near the Trool Fair. That\'s really all I know about it. When they noticed I was getting a bit close for comfort, they lowered their voices considerably.";
D.q[5527] = "Thanks a lot. Now I just need you to sign here and the document\'s official. If you don\'t validate the document, I\'ll have to cancel the whole thing and you\'ll lose your money.";
D.q[5163] = "";
D.q[5822] = "";
D.q[1423] = "#1, you\'re an Amaknean again.";
D.q[6025] = "I don\'t have anything to say to you, go on your way.";
D.q[6803] = "Wait, I... no, nothing.";
D.q[7281] = "";
D.q[7006] = "Meuh Sieurchance should swallow half of the Sacred Water. The other half should be taken to Dragonsly at the Astrub Alchemists\' Market so that he can transmute it with his Moon Water.\nOnce the transmutation is complete, use the liquid to forge a Dontase Mebro Shovel, which I\'ll then use on Meuh Sieurchance.";
D.q[1571] = "As you wish.";
D.q[7032] = "You\'ll need the help of several people. A member of the Order of the Salvatory Spirit who is at least a Follower of Writing, a Xelor that can master the spell \'Clock\' and a Sacrier that can master the spell \'Flying Sword\'. Various craftsmen should also accompany you, and they must be masters in their art. A Jeweller and a Jewelmagus, a Staff Carver and a Staff Carvemage, a Dagger Smith and a Dagger Smithmagus, and finally an alchemist. No need to bring individual craftsmen along if one person has several of these professions.\nBefore I forget, do not forget to bring 5 Diamond Stones, 1 Crystal, 1 Mother of Pearl and 1 Tsunami Potion.\nI already reserved nine seats with Nikos Monote in Cania Bay, to take you and your companions to the Isle O\'Anstitch. If you need more people, you must pay for the extra places yourself.";
D.q[6027] = "Greetings. How was your trip to Otomai Island? Have you any news about the Dofus?";
D.q[7364] = "";
D.q[5548] = "";
D.q[6906] = "Really? I suppose that the thief is the person who came to see me, which would mean that I\'m partly at fault for the theft as it was me that told the thief.\nI know the location of another of these hammers, but I must warn you: it was used to seal the crypt of a powerful vampire. Therefore, if you take the hammer, the vampire will be free to go out and haunt Amakna at will. As you belong to the militia of the City of Light, I suppose you are able to gather enough forces to destroy this monster, which is why I\'ll help you find it.\nThe underground crypt is accessible through another crypt in the Amakna Cemetery, but I do not know which one. However, I think that a book in Library of Brakmar, recounts the history of the hammer and how it was hidden in the crypt. It certainly shows how to open the underground passage. Bring it to me and we\'ll have a look at it together.";
D.q[7282] = "";
D.q[7365] = "";
D.q[2657] = "What? You\'ve lost your shield and you haven\'t even started your training?\nI can make you another one, but you\'ll have to bring me 10 pieces of Bamboo Wood.";
D.q[6197] = "";
D.q[6196] = "";
D.q[5827] = "";
D.q[7044] = "I am here on the orders of Danathor, Quartermaster of Bonta. As for the reason behind my presence in this cave, it is none of your concern.";
D.q[30] = "Well, we don\'t sit around doing nothing with my little Shika...We are snowed under with work! \nFortunately the crops are growing well this year...\n\nIf you have time, I\'ve got work for you.";
D.q[7007] = "I guess it\'s to make a Dontase Mebro Shovel?\nIf one of your friends needs such critical treatment, it is my duty to help you as an Eniripsa.\nI\'ll get right on the transmutation. If you don\'t yet know how to use the Dontase Mebro Shovel, take one of these, you\'ll need it.\nThere, the transmutation is complete. You can now build a Dontase Mebro Shovel. Say hello to Shaman Surivitna for me.";
D.q[2602] = "Mmh... You haven\'t paid your taxes! I\'m sorry but I can\'t talk to you...";
D.q[5551] = "";
D.q[3174] = "What are you doing in my Tofu House? Did you know that we\'ve been breeding Tofus for several generations? We\'re even breeding unique species on the continent!";
D.q[7045] = "I\'m assuming Danathor gave you the instructions. I\'m here to coordinate the work and use the Hammer of Light to a weapon of unparalleled power, except that of the Dofus, it goes without saying.\nLet your companions take their places, and do not worry if there are less of them than the apparent number of spaces. As long as they correspond to the instructions and you possess the necessary items, it should be fine.\nPosition yourself in front of the anvil with all of the necessary materials and we will begin, unless you lack something.";
D.q[5828] = "";
D.q[1467] = "Whik livik wititik ivik biknik jilis,\nis likik tik ink whik slips wititik ink limp.\nHik cinik fik tik irik cimiknik ti hik hik,\nbik cinik nik sik ik.\n\n";
D.q[6198] = "";
D.q[2189] = "Hummm... let me think... you\'ve got your wood out, so I reckon you want a bow job, right? Alright... but you\'ll have to hand over quite a few Kamas!";
D.q[5286] = "";
D.q[6030] = "Yes, you\'re deisturbing me. But now that you\'re here, you might as well tell me why you came.";
D.q[258] = "Hello, I\'m Aria Knofob. I recently settled in the Province of Amakna and I really thought I was lucky to get this house for a few Kamas.\nIt\'s a magnificent setting but the surrounding woods are stuffed with Arachnees. They\'re attracted to light, too, so the house is overrun with them. They live in the attic!";
D.q[6200] = "";
D.q[5830] = "";
D.q[3079] = "Another day full of action. Watch your teeth by the way!";
D.q[3076] = "I didn\'t mean a real shark (which comes from the words sharp and skidmark, by the way), he\'s a gangster, a bully, a lout who\'s causing commotion in the harbour. You can\'t miss him, he\'s a sanguine fellow (or red, to an ignoramus like you). Tell him to leave the region!";
D.q[3623] = "You take Pinkgob.";
D.q[4743] = "";
D.q[7284] = "";
D.q[6201] = "";
D.q[5832] = "";
D.q[7046] = "Hurry up and take that to Danathor, he must be impatient to offer it to Jiva.";
D.q[7285] = "";
D.q[3628] = "Piwi win Bwork! BASTAWWWD! Try more!";
D.q[7008] = "To forge a Dontase Mebro Shovel, you\'ll need to find a shovel smith. Yes, I know, it seems obvious to you, but it isn\'t for everyone. You must then assemble the following resources: 1 Transmuted Water, 10 Crackler\'s Golden Teeth, 2 Aluminite, 1 Magnesite and 10 Maple Wood.\nI forgot: it is essential that you bring me the shovel\'s user manual, Dragonsly should have one. Get one when you go see him.";
D.q[5211] = "";
D.q[6807] = "Hello, do you need help?";
D.q[6032] = "Greetings. What is a disciple of Jiva doing here? I suppose you have something to ask me?";
D.q[2242] = "*Gazing at a small flax flower*\nLook at this beauty! This is a gift from Nature - a true marvel so delicately given to us. Let\'s take care of it and preserve it.";
D.q[6204] = "";
D.q[6203] = "";
D.q[1977] = "So? I\'m still waiting for that report!";
D.q[7047] = "What are you still doing here? Hurry to the Isle O\'Anstitch and forge the Dawn Shard. I cannot wait to give it to the great Jiva.";
D.q[2014] = "Pnj(473) et Message(2012)";
D.q[1350] = "*Paper*\nWha...? I lost. You\'re not too bad... Round two!";
D.q[4843] = "*Questions everyone again and calls you to the witness box once more*\nI will only ask you this once. In your opinion, is Kit Dingaround innocent or guilty?";
D.q[6808] = "Yes, sir. I\'ll take a zaapi straight away.";
D.q[4750] = "";
D.q[7286] = "";
D.q[4594] = "...Oto Mustam\'s orders. I have to get the documents no matter what...\nHmm, we have ourselves a troublemaker.";
D.q[4401] = "... That\'s wonderful. Well it seems it wasn\'t him after all, but I\'m going to keep a close eye on him just to be sure.";
D.q[6951] = "Woah theresshhh, not ssshhho fasssshhht... That\'sssshhh not how we meetsssshhh the masssshhhter... Tell meeeessshh whysshhhh you\'re here firssssshhhht.";
D.q[681] = "I, Don Rouann, am so very sad\nTo find so many people who are glad\nJust because they forgot they forgot \nA little thing that means a lot.";
D.q[7011] = "Flutterthoughts? Few people are aware of their existence, and fewer still are those that can hunt them. Let me explain how they work.\nIn the Dragoturkey Territory, near Agony V\'Helley, there is a dark tower. It is at the foot of the tower that the flutterthoughts live, and nowhere else.\nSome very particular, tiny caterpillars are born in the flower fields around the tower. Once they have captured a lost thought, they form a cocoon, commonly called a chrysalis, to become flutterthoughts a few weeks later. If the pupa is destroyed before maturity, the thought is lost forever.";
D.q[682] = "Then a new hope came to enlighten me.\nIn your person searching to understand,\nthis secret to you I\'ll teach,\nYes I\'ll teach you.";
D.q[7394] = "";
D.q[840] = "Aaah, even a demon appreciates a break every once in a while.\nMy son is still bugging me... wants to fight me... the cocky beggar. All the same, it\'s better than waiting for my special agents to come back.\nHemm, you don\'t have anything to do right now, do you? Go entertain my son then. And you\'d better lose the fight, otherwise I\'ll have to beat you myself.";
D.q[7838] = "Did Bambelle send you?\nOh no, it was Gormor. Nevermind, it\'s the same thing. Thank him for me, and tell him I need more.";
D.q[5508] = "A Bontarian in the militia. Get out of here before I kill you and take your quintessence away!";
D.q[5491] = "What rank do you wish to have in the militia?";
D.q[5233] = "";
D.q[7012] = "It is not really possible to identify a lost thought, although Greu Nouille and I have already identified certain categories. For example, flutterthoughts related to the lost thoughts of exceptional beings are easily identifiable by their unique features. The more the thought is lost, the more impressive the flutterthought is, and that\'s without mentioning the colours of its wings.\nWe also found that each disciple of the gods has its own form of flutterthought. Iops, for example, often lose the thread of their thoughts. For this reason their flutterthoughts are numerous, but small.\nIf you intend to capture a flutterthought, heed this warning: whoever touches a flutterthought becomes amnesiac, that\'s what happened to me recently.";
D.q[7839] = "Take those and be careful. Wild creatures roam nearby.";
D.q[284] = "Well, why not! I\'ll pay you if you bring me some crab claws. For each lot of three, you\'ll get poppy seeds... good bakers use them to flavour their bread.";
D.q[1504] = "The first wave has passed...\nHey you! I hope you\'re here to help!";
D.q[3850] = "Well, well... another young soul looking for adventure on Incarnam...";
D.q[3307] = "Which books were published since I last came to the library? How to serve a Bontarian? How to stamp on a Piwi? Maybe I should go have a look...";
D.q[7013] = "For a novice like you, it\'d be mission impossible. However, Greu Nouille, my pretty Feca, is the best flutterthought hunter in the World of Twelve. If you tell her that I sent you, she\'ll agree to help you. After all, am I not her favourite companion?";
D.q[6954] = "Don\'t you think I\'ve already got enough on my plate as it is? It\'s nice that you thought of me, but I really don\'t have the time.";
D.q[7287] = "";
D.q[7840] = "There\'s not enough, you\'ll have to come back tomorrow.";
D.q[2834] = "Last night, Brakmarians burnt several food stores which held food for the Militia\'s Dragoturkeys. The reserves are eaten up fast, so we\'ll need to find a way to grow cereals quicker. Merlinmagus Ambrosius, in the alchemists workshop, can help you.\n\nI\'m counting on you.";
D.q[7395] = "";
D.q[7841] = "Through our efforts, the sea route to Amakna has been reopened. It\'s a great achievement.\nIf we continue like this, we should be able to completely thaw the port and then maybe it will regain some of its former glory.";
D.q[4398] = "Ahh! Who are you? No, I was taken.\nI\'ll tell you the truth... I was hooked on Ouassingue juice. If I didn\'t have a mouthful every day, I just couldn\'t concentrate on a thing. You\'re not going to turn me in, are you?";
D.q[4600] = "Ah, so you\'re from Bonta? I found the documents as expected... what I didn\'t expect is that they\'d follow me!\nAh, I hear them... they\'re coming!";
D.q[6955] = "Do you a little favour in Amakna? If it\'s well paid, then yes, I\'m interested, rrrrawr. I\'ve always wanted to visit King Allister\'s castle, as well.";
D.q[2336] = "I...voiceless...come back...later...!";
D.q[7396] = "";
D.q[4696] = "";
D.q[5101] = "";
D.q[6956] = "Hmpf...the cemetery? Well... I\'m not sure... The tombs make me uncomfortable and knowing I\'m surrounded by corpses... brrr, it makes my hairs stand on end. I\'m sorry, but I prefer the comfort of the tavern and the company of militiamen and noble people.";
D.q[7842] = "Previously, we used this port for exporting large quantities of agricultural resources. There were boats everywhere and people were constantly busy on the docks, they were swarming all over the place.\nNow the quays are deserted and the boats trapped in ice.";
D.q[7397] = "";
D.q[545] = "Between you and me, it\'s a long story full of gold, monkeys and disreputable characters. All I can remember is an explosion, flying through the air in a boat, tearing the sail off to use it as a parachute and then ending up with my head buried in the sand.";
D.q[5841] = "";
D.q[5842] = "";
D.q[1012] = "Back already? I\'ll study the information you brought me on the door of Brakmar calmly. \nAnyway, I\'ve got a new job for you. An aggressive wild boar tramples on the harvests in the South of the city. Try to chase it away to calm farmers down.";
D.q[6809] = "This militiaman has come to guard my paddock. Do I have you to thank for that?";
D.q[7843] = "I cut quite the athlete carrying tonnes and tonnes of tonnes of grain. Given that we no longer export anything these days, I converted to transporting heavy materials, especially the planks and the metal used for the pipework.";
D.q[6957] = "Mmm, I could be interested. Tell me more.";
D.q[7014] = "One of Solar\'s Flutterthoughts? That\'s not too bad, they\'re not the hardest thing to find. Solar\'s Flutterthoughts are golden and glistening and leave a trail of light in their wake. The main difficulty in capturing one comes from the fact that there aren\'t many of them and also the height at which they fly. I\'ll have to climb the tower to have a hope of catching one.\nI\'m helping you because Meuh Sieurchance told me that you cured his amnesia. Take this as a sign of my gratitude.\nNow, wait for me here, I\'ve just seen the Flutterthought you need.";
D.q[7398] = "";
D.q[6377] = "BwaaAAK!";
D.q[4704] = "";
D.q[7015] = "...";
D.q[4702] = "It\'s a bit weak, really. It confirms Kit Dingaround\'s activities on the day of his arrest but it doesn\'t prove he is innocent. It must be investigated further and I\'m counting on you to get my friend off the hook.";
D.q[1138] = "Some of them are a bit dented, you should have been more delicate with them.\nAnyway, that should be ok. You\'ll soon be one of us #1.";
D.q[7844] = "Frigost is going through a bad patch and our mayor is doing everything she can to get us through it.\nGo and visit her and see how motivated she is for yourself.";
D.q[6958] = "If there are a few of them it could be good fun. I already have an idea of how I\'ll treat them, they won\'t forget it in a hurry. Mouhahaha, OK, I\'ll visit these people. They should contact me with a date so I can organise my appointments.";
D.q[5118] = "";
D.q[4677] = "Before I spread your guts all over the walls I\'ve a little mission for you. Normally it\'s the young recruits that would carry it out but your recent failure merits punishment.\nIf the horn is as powerful as they say it\'s Bonta has gained a formidable weapon indeed! We should prepare ourselves for an attack! \nGive one of these crates to the following warriors. They\'ll need it to improve their equipment - Brank Thoof, Kad Maxy, Jack Rottance, and Xale DuGros.";
D.q[7019] = "Hello, have you come to relieve me?";
D.q[7366] = "";
D.q[6959] = "The prices varies according to the weight and age of the animal. If you see one you want, just say so.";
D.q[7016] = "Well, it was easier than I\'d expected. While trying to catch the flutterthought I found this chrysalis. Take it, and be very careful not to damage it. Pupae like that are very rare. Now you\'d better go, I look forward to seeing you again soon.";
D.q[778] = "68";
D.q[787] = "77";
D.q[806] = "96";
D.q[873] = "63";
D.q[7017] = "Hello, I can see by your face that you\'re bringing me good news. I\'m listening.";
D.q[588] = "Well, you don\'t make a very good Kanniball, but you do make a great fighter, and I\'m very impressed by your skill. As a reward for defeating me, I\'ll show you my secret technique for throwing hammers. I\'ll also let you use it in my name. If you don\'t mind, though, I\'ll have to ask you to leave the village as soon as possible.";
D.q[899] = "89";
D.q[4715] = "";
D.q[6960] = "I\'ll give you one for 10,000 Kamas! A golden opportunity not to be missed!\nOkay, thanks to you I have a militiaman watching over my paddock, so I\'ll accept 8,000 Kamas. No less. 8,000 Kamas, take it or leave it.";
D.q[572] = "Ah, there\'s also a local tribe. They\'re great cooks, but I don\'t recommend you try their food! Hahaha! They also make beautiful masks. Ohoh.";
D.q[7018] = "It\'s magnificent. We\'ll be able to forge a weapon of such beauty with it that it will be worthy of Jiva herself.\nLook after this item well, we\'ll need it later.";
D.q[600] = "You seem very determined so I won\'t hold you back. Take that rope, tie it round your neck like a necklace and you\'re ready to go! Enjoy your trip and send us a postcard!";
D.q[7846] = "You were fast, for a tourist. Thank you, thanks to you we will soon be able to resume normal activity.\nSeveral fishermen have reported that they are missing parts that can only be manufactured in the city.\nGo see Valy Domidat, Frigost\'s handywoman, and give her this list.";
D.q[7472] = "";
D.q[417] = "Though Amakna itself is quite peaceful, the same cannot be said of the surrounding country.\nIf you stay close to the town, you should be okay - they usually won\'t strike the first blow.\nThe farther you move away from the centre of Amakna the more aggressive these creatures are. They may attack you for no reason.\nStay in the village if you\'re not accompanied by other adventurers, or you might have an unpleasant encounter.";
D.q[7823] = "Fishing has become increasingly difficult and the fact that the drills often break down doesn\'t help.\nWe have to keep going though, because agriculture in greenhouses is not enough to feed all the mouths and we must change food from time to time to have a balanced diet.\nEat and exercise, as Herr Peece, our doctor, would say.";
D.q[610] = "You want to buy it yourself? Why not, it\'d save me a great deal of time. I let you have it for 5,000 Kamas and 5 orange larva skins. I need the skins to make an invisibility potion. A that price, it\'s a steal.";
D.q[7473] = "";
D.q[6965] = "";
D.q[3566] = "Ahahaha! Me have got beautiful gift. Female admire me!";
D.q[7847] = "Damar needs my help? He\'s taking the mickey!\nTell him I\'m still waiting for the ring he promised me thirty years ago, so he can wait for his equipment.";
D.q[6966] = "Thissssshhhh boar is very fat, which issssshhh jussssshhhht how I like them. Teranssssshhhhhhe will contact the ladiesssshhhh in Bonta, would you like to ssssshhhee Vil Smisssssshhhhe now?";
D.q[6209] = "If I were you I\'d think long and hard about this. Many militiamen patrol these parts - all I\'ve to do is scream and they\'ll come running. \nIf you want some excitement, why don\'t you go buy one of our charming hostesses a drink.";
D.q[7289] = "";
D.q[6649] = "";
D.q[1152] = "My name is Oshimo Li\'Kross Babine. I\'ve come a very long way to share my knowledge of pets with you. When I heard the rumour of the new Pet Plague, I rushed here with my Tabi. In the end, I decided to stay.";
D.q[7848] = "Pfft, is she still moaning on about that ring? It\'s not my fault, I lost it hunting the Royal Pingwin. Will you go and get it back for me and take it to Valy with my apologies?";
D.q[6320] = "Oh that... you know, it\'s not much. I only make things when I\'ve an order... nothing more.";
D.q[7021] = "I was expecting you. You must now get your hands on the tears of the goddess Sacrier. I would suggest that Chaki Triss, in the Temple of Sacrier would be in the best position to be able to tell you more about it.\nCome back and see me when you have the Sacrier\'s Tears, not before.";
D.q[7022] = "Greetings, I suppose you\'ve brought me the Sacrier\'s Tears that I asked for. So, where are they?";
D.q[3475] = "Bworks no show off now. Workshops no for goblins. You great defensor of Goblins. Me give gift.";
D.q[1821] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Iop temple.\nIt will cost you a Flint.";
D.q[7849] = "He\'s finally made up his mind. I would have preferred him to come himself, but he was probably afraid of how I\'d react.\nFor the trouble, I\'ll make him wait a little longer, after thirty years of waiting, he deserves that much, right?";
D.q[6962] = "Have you swallowed a sad clown or something? Well, if this is the boar then you want, I\'ll make you an unbeatable offers. 1,000 Kamas. Buy now, no discount, and I do not accept credit.\nPlease check your change as mistakes cannot be rectified later.";
D.q[3519] = "Hum hum yum yum, me devour your heart!!!";
D.q[265] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Cra temple.\nIt will cost you a Flax String. \n";
D.q[7850] = "She wants me to wait? Who does she think I am, some kind of Iop?\nOh, you think it\'s funny, do you? Take that and get out of my sight.";
D.q[7290] = "";
D.q[3478] = "Me no lil\'gob, me great Goblin chief!";
D.q[6920] = "Hello, you\'ve arrived at the right time. Ebru Of El let me know that he was looking for you. It\'s about the hammer you found, apparently he still needs your help.";
D.q[5082] = "";
D.q[1814] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Eniripsa temple.\nIt will cost you a Coco Blop Flower.";
D.q[3564] = "Prespic set and a wand.";
D.q[5337] = "";
D.q[5371] = "";
D.q[1806] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Enutrof temple.\nIt will cost you a Gold Ingot.";
D.q[7291] = "";
D.q[6968] = "There are plenty of opportunities for us to make Kamas, but there\'s one thing that I covet and my men have not yet managed to approach it. A crate was delivered to Bonta, but unfortunately it is protected by a powerful magic that rejects any attempt at opening it. After much effort, my Rogues finally discovered how to approach the crate. Only devout servants of Bonta can access it, provided they are a follower of one of the city\'s three Guardians.\nBasically, only Bontarians who have at least the third title of their Order can approach the crate.\nBring me the crate and in return I will find a way to contact the Demons of the Hours.";
D.q[7474] = "";
D.q[858] = "Fight against the devilish son of the Master!";
D.q[6142] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6969] = "As you wish. When you realise you have no other choice, come back and see me. Hahaha.";
D.q[5338] = "";
D.q[638] = "If you\'re looking for recipes, you should go to the library. An alchemist created an encyclopedia composed of more than 12 books about rare recipes.";
D.q[4792] = "I was just curious, there\'s no harm in that.";
D.q[7475] = "";
D.q[1156] = "The amount of money depends on its general state, if it has eaten or not... In fact, if it\'s hungry you\'ll have to pay a contractual amount for opening the file...\nThe amount of money to take it back depends on the number of days we passed taking care of it and add it another contractual amount depending on the kind of pet you have.";
D.q[6970] = "Only devout servants of Bonta can access the crate, provided they follow the path of one of the three Guardians of the City. Basically, only Bontarians with at least the third title of their Order can approach it.\nTry to remember that.";
D.q[3506] = "You\'re the only one who can find what I need. I\'m shut away in here because of my people and my overdeveloped brain.";
D.q[7292] = "";
D.q[7476] = "";
D.q[1786] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Osamodas temple.\nIt will cost you Gobball saliva.";
D.q[3486] = "Only for a Bwork, that\'s why these two tribes live together. It\'s the only species that Bworks don\'t like to eat. Only Bwork magus eat them when they begin their training to learn how to read. Every night, I dream about this battle. My mother Bworkcelhain was fed up with hearing my screams.";
D.q[7058] = "Now head back to your Order Master, they have an important mission to entrust you with.";
D.q[5340] = "Maybe if we move slowly and logically...";
D.q[7661] = "Thank you adventurer, we\'re no longer corrupted by the Brakmarian magic. When Goultard comes, we won\'t have to attack him. There\'s just one thing left for you to do: tale this cursed item to the Iop temple. Goultard\'s father will know what to do with it!";
D.q[1831] = "If you want to challenge a Dopple, you must make a donation to the Sadida temple.\nIt will cost you a Leaf of Trunknid.";
D.q[772] = "62";
D.q[7477] = "";
D.q[2764] = "When you feel ready, come to the Dojo on a Saturday. You\'ll have to demonstrate your techniques to gain a new level.";
D.q[7293] = "";
D.q[734] = "Today is a very pleasant day.";
D.q[6972] = "I remember you, I got the runsssssshhh after I roassssshhhht that boar. The meat wasssshhh rotten and I\'ve sssshhhtill got sssshhhtomacsssshhh crampssssshhh. I\'ll make you pay for that...";
D.q[6973] = "Psssshhhh, you got away with it thisssshhh time, nexsssshhhht time you won\'t be ssssshhhho lucky, I assssshhhhhhure you.";
D.q[6243] = "If you\'re looking for something on the black market, go see Rekojel. He knows each and every product that circulates in the city, which means that he knows about everything that\'s bought and sold in the city. You can find him near the public paddocks, not far from the handymen\'s workshop.";
D.q[7294] = "";
D.q[435] = "If you bring me 10 White Dreggon Eggs, I\'ll give you an Old Dreggon Bone in exchange. \nIt\'s a magic bone, Azra Lazarus the Jeweller is convinced that it can be used to make precious jewels. \nGo and see her, she\'ll give you more details.";
D.q[7426] = "";
D.q[856] = "46";
D.q[857] = "47";
D.q[4033] = "Oh yeah! Of course, Wabbit teeth! Unfortunately, I used all I had for my previous potion... Can you go and collect the ingredients, please?";
D.q[3232] = "Well, you certainly took your time! Did you actually manage to get lost on this island?\nIf you want to leave, it\'s now or never! I can take you back for only 200 Kamas, it\'s not even twice as expensive as a one-way ticket! \nWipe that look off your face. This time we\'ll be going against the current, so the hull of my ship will wear out a lot more!";
D.q[1810] = "Since many Eniripsas want to train with my Dopples, I ask them to make a donation before each fight to support the temple.\nIf you want to challenge a Dopple, bring me a Dandelion Flower.";
D.q[6974] = "Your friend from Bonta wassssshhhhh a bit heavy-handed, I have to sssshhhhay. I had a good time with her, but now I ache all over...";
D.q[2951] = "What a pity... But I do understand how you feel. A long time ago, I went through the same thing. By the way, I forgot to tell you the good news. I\'m in the middle of some important repairs to my church... Now, I don\'t like to do this, but before I can annul your marriage and declare your divorce, well, maybe you could help... How about a modest 10,000 Kamas for a new cassock, 15,000 Kamas to redo all the church windows, 5,000 Kamas to take care of my beard, and 20,000 Kamas to buy a few drops of communion wine... All together, I\'d need 50,000 Kamas. Bless you!!!";
D.q[2579] = "If you say no, I\'ll be very insulted. If you insult me, you insult all the Pandawas, not to mention our goddess... And if you do that, you\'ll find it difficult to get any information at all about the Dofus of Pandala... That\'s why you came isn\'t it?";
D.q[39] = "Hi, I\'m Hanniball Smisse, the Grand Blacksmith of a renowned secret Team. I\'ve not seen my comrades since our last secret operation, though. Try to find them and get back to me as soon as possible.";
D.q[3942] = "What? A Wabbit transformation potion? It sounds complicated and I don\'t have the knowledge to make it on my own... I need help from my colleagues in Amakna. Would you mind paying them a visit for me? One is in the north-west, the other in the south and the last at the centre of Amakna.";
D.q[7399] = "";
D.q[1691] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[1692] = "Choose your prize.";
D.q[616] = "He asked me for some information on the victim. At first, I thought he was just an onlooker but well, I looked harder and decidcd he must be a suspect.\nI vaguely told him it was about the killing of the landlord and asked him where he was the night before at around 8 p.m.";
D.q[3974] = "Whaaat? Killed Wabbit? No inter, inter, no funny for big Bwork like me.";
D.q[423] = "Srams are the daggers specialists. Daggers are quite fast but generally don\'t cause much damage. On the other hand, their critical hits are really impressive. \nAgility is essential to properly handle Daggers. Indeed, as a close combat weapon, you need to be able to approach, hit and run away from your enemy.\nDagger Smiths use the Dagger Smith Hammer.";
D.q[4522] = "If you go looking by yourself it\'ll take you months. You should go ask Setag the Enutrof, that old miner must know some places it\'s hard to get to... where I\'d be safer than I\'m here.";
D.q[1015] = "Poor Gobballs, you\'re not the most sensitive, are you #1? You have to have exactly the right number!\nUnless you don\'t know how to count, of course?\nI\'ll take these ones for now, but you still have to bring me 32 more!";
D.q[7059] = "The following stones...";
D.q[606] = "Hahaha, if you don\'t want to sleep under the stars you\'ll have to build a house or at least a roof of some kind. You\'ll need to cut down some Kokonut palms. With one Kokobut Palm Trunk, you can easily make a wooden plank, and with two you can make a little wooden beam. Go see the wannabe pirate south of the beach, he has his own workshop there. That way I won\'t have to lend you my tools. Hahaha!";
D.q[425] = "Hammers are the favourite weapons of Osamodas and Xelors. In general, they require a little strength and a great deal of intelligence to be handled. Indeed, most hammers have powerful magical properties.\nHammer Smiths use the Hammer Smith Hammer.";
